	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64410160"><p><div class="quote"><p> <i>in recognition of the fact that what the various inventors are really claiming is a means of bypassing Newton's third law.</i><span class="substr"> </span> </p></div><p>&gt; <i>Oh, Newton made law that says propellant free drives do not exist?</i> <br>
 <b>Yes, Newton' third law: every action has an equal and opposite reaction. In physics, usually phrased as "law of conservation of momentum": if you push mass in one direction, you have to push other mass in the other direction such that the sum of the momentum is zero.</b> </p><p>&gt; <i>How does a Mag Lev Train work then?</i> <br>
 <b>Magnetic fields push down on the Earth.</b> </p><p>&gt; <i>How does an MHD submarine drive work?</i> <br>
 <b>Electromagnetic forces pus</b></p></div>
	</div>

